METHODOLOGY:
The bill requires voters of all towns served by a school district to vote on closing any school. It
also requires school boards to hold a public meeting for the vote, using the same process for both
singledistrictandcooperativedistricts.
Local school districts would be responsible for providing notice and managing related procedures
in the event of a public meeting for the vote of a school closure. If a school within the district is
closed,thedistrictmayincuradditionalexpenses.
